article.headline: High Point 67, Savannah St. 51
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. (AP) -- Arizona Reid got his fourth consecutive double-double, scoring 28 points and grabbing 14 rebounds to lead High Point to a 67-51 victory over Savannah State on Tuesday night. Mike Jefferson and Tim Burns had 13 points each for the Panthers (6-4), who have now won eight consecutive home games. The Tigers (6-9) got 10 points each from Joseph Flegler and Chris Linton. The teams were tied at 26-26 at halftime, then again at 36-36 with 11:56 remaining. But High Point went on a 14-3 run, taking a 50-39 lead at the five-minute mark. The Panthers maintained a double-digit lead from that point on.
